                                    "date_end": 1246251600,
                                    "appointing_president": "George H. W. Bush",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2686"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32703,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 42141,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/david_souter.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 6839,
                            "identifier": "david_h_souter"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 4.709,
                                "stop": 13.442,
                                "byte_start": 47585,
                                "byte_stop": 82484,
                                "text": "The first of the two is No. 02-1080, General Dynamics Land Systems against Cline."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 13.442,
                                "stop": 17.078,
                                "byte_start": 82484,
                                "byte_stop": 97008,
                                "text": "This case comes to us on writ of certiorari to the Sixth Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 17.078,
                                "stop": 34.668,
                                "byte_start": 97008,
                                "byte_stop": 167434,
                                "text": "In 1997 a collective bargaining agreement between petitioner, General Dynamics, and United Auto Workers eliminated the company\u2019s obligation to provide health benefits to subsequently retired employees except as to then current workers at least 50 years old."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 34.668,
                                "stop": 43.666,
                                "byte_start": 167434,
                                "byte_stop": 203379,
                                "text": "Respondents are a group of workers under 50 who brought this action in Federal Court under the Age Discrimination and Employment Act, the ADEA."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 43.666,
                                "stop": 51.034,
                                "byte_start": 203379,
                                "byte_stop": 232845,
                                "text": "They challenge the favorable treatment of the older employees on a theory of what the District Court called reverse age discrimination."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 51.034,
                                "stop": 58.2,
                                "byte_start": 232845,
                                "byte_stop": 261475,
                                "text": "The Court observed that no court had ever granted relief under the ADEA on such a claim and dismissed the complaint."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 58.2,
                                "stop": 79.508,
                                "byte_start": 261475,
                                "byte_stop": 346739,
                                "text": "On appeal, a divided panel of the Sixth Circuit reversed with the majority reasoning that the ADEA\u2019s prohibition of discrimination against \u201cany individual because of such individual\u2019s age\u201d is so clear in its face that if Congress had meant to limit its coverage to protect only the older worker against the younger, it would have said so."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 79.508,
                                "stop": 86.954,
                                "byte_start": 346739,
                                "byte_stop": 376519,
                                "text": "We granted certiorari to resolve the resulting conflict among the Circuits."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 86.954,
                                "stop": 91.165,
                                "byte_start": 376519,
                                "byte_stop": 393341,
                                "text": "In an opinion filed today with he Clerk of the Court, we reverse."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 91.165,
                                "stop": 97.67,
                                "byte_start": 393341,
                                "byte_stop": 419359,
                                "text": "The common ground in this case that the ADEA forbids discriminatory preference for the young over the old."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 97.67,
                                "stop": 102.64,
                                "byte_start": 419359,
                                "byte_stop": 439317,
                                "text": "The question is whether it also prohibits favoring the old over the young."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 102.64,
                                "stop": 108.834,
                                "byte_start": 439317,
                                "byte_stop": 464081,
                                "text": "In the abstract, the ADEA\u2019s reference simply to age could be read either way."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 108.834,
                                "stop": 117.655,
                                "byte_start": 464081,
                                "byte_stop": 499294,
                                "text": "The more expansive possible understanding does not however square over the natural reading of the whole provision prohibiting discrimination."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 117.655,
                                "stop": 133.093,
                                "byte_start": 499294,
                                "byte_stop": 561048,
                                "text": "In common experience along with the congressional testimony, reports, and findings simply confirm that Congress used the phrase discrimination because of an individual\u2019s age the same way that ordinary people in common usage might speak of age discrimination any day of the week."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 133.093,
                                "stop": 141.608,
                                "byte_start": 561048,
                                "byte_stop": 595111,
                                "text": "That is as showing that the statute does not mean to stop an employer from favoring an older employee over a younger one."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 141.608,
                                "stop": 165.739,
                                "byte_start": 595111,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Scalia filed a dissenting opinion; Justice Thomas has also filed a dissenting opinion in which Justice Kennedy joins."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
